# Refactor Agent Rules — TaskFlow AI

- Tighten Pydantic models: `ConfigDict(strict=True)` where appropriate
- Ensure nh3 (backend) and DOMPurify (frontend) on all user HTML paths
- Remove duplication; keep repository pattern consistent
- AgentResultEnvelope consistency (MVP 3+)

## Agentic refactoring loop (ADR-004)

When performing large or multi-file refactors:

1. Prefer deterministic AST renames via `backend/refactoring/` over guessed text edits
2. Never apply patches without human-approved finding IDs
3. Snapshot before patch; verify; rollback on failure
4. Record accept/reject + verify outcomes for feedback
5. Stay inside `REFACTORING_SANDBOX_ROOT` when using the API
6. Use inline (this Cursor agent) for small local edits; use `/api/v1/refactoring/*` for goal-driven multi-file cleanup

See `docs/adr/ADR-004-ai-code-refactoring-alignment.md`.

